<chapter xml:id="sec-ncx" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.1b2"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>NCX Documents</title>

    <section xml:id="sec-ncx-introduction">
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para> In order to enable ease of navigation and provide greater accessibility, EPUB
            Publications support a "Navigation Center eXtended," the NCX. The NCX was originally
            standardized by the DAISY Consortium, as defined by Section 8 of the DAISY/NISO Standard
            formally called ANSI/NISO Z39.86-2005, Specifications for the Digital Talking Book. The
            EPUB specification defines its own schema (XML grammar) for the NCX content type, as
            some multimedia and metadata components from the DAISY specification are not included. </para>
        <para> The NCX exposes the hierarchical structure of an EPUB Publication to allow the user
            to navigate through it. The NCX is similar to a table of contents in that it enables the
            reader to jump directly to any of the major structural elements of the document, i.e.
            part, chapter, or section, but it will often contain more elements of the document than
            the publisher chooses to include in the original print table of contents. It can be
            visualized as a collapsible tree familiar to PC users. Its development was motivated by
            the need to provide quick access to the main structural elements of a document without
            the need to parse the entire documents. Other elements such as pages, footnotes,
            figures, tables, etc. can be included in separate, nonhierarchical lists. </para>
        <!-- 
        <para role="rsconf"<Reading Systems must provide a means to navigate a Publication based on
            the information in its NCX file.</para> -->
    </section>

    <section xml:id="sec-ncx-content-conf">
        <title>NCX Document Content Conformance</title>

        <simplelist role="conformance-list">
            <member role="conformance-item">An NCX Document must be a well-formed XML Document <xref
                    linkend="refXML"/>.</member>
            <member role="conformance-item">An NCX Document must be encoded in UTF-8 or UTF-16 <xref
                    linkend="refUnicode5"/>.</member>
            <member role="conformance-item">An NCX Document must be valid to the NCX Document schema
                as defined in <xref linkend="app-ncx-schema"/>, and in addition must conform to all
                content conformance constraints expressed in <xref linkend="sec-ncx-def"/>.</member>
            <member role="conformance-item">The NCX Document filename should use the file extension
                    <filename>.ncx</filename>. Any document fragments (included via XML entities or
                XInclude) should not use the <filename>.ncx</filename> extension. <xref
                    linkend="refXML"/>
                <xref linkend="refXInclude"/></member>
        </simplelist>
    </section>

